<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1404102-but-why-is-it-named-gotham-isn-t-that-bat">But why is it named Gotham? Isn&#39;t that Bat Man&#39;s fictional city? I found this book while looking for Bat Man books.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1404102'><a id="like_count_community_question_1404102" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1404102?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F217329.Gotham">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1404102-but-why-is-it-named-gotham-isn-t-that-bat">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1404102-but-why-is-it-named-gotham-isn-t-that-bat">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/2763879-martha"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1448650870i/2763879._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2763879-martha">Martha</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Washington Irving gave NY that nickname in his literary magazine Salmagundi in 1807. It means goat town and was the name of a perhaps fictional town i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Washington Irving gave NY that nickname in his literary magazine Salmagundi in 1807. It means goat town and was the name of a perhaps fictional town in old English legend whose inhabitants pretended to be stupid in order to trick rulers out of cheating or oppressing them. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link762203" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=762203&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1404102-but-why-is-it-named-gotham-isn-t-that-bat%2Fanswers%2F762203-washington-irving-gave">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

