  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2265301818" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2265301818" />
    <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro"><img alt="Michael Finocchiaro" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576692048p2/48483884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2265301818?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Finocchiaro" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro">Michael Finocchiaro</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=new-york-city">new-york-city</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=american-21st-c">american-21st-c</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=pulitzer-history">pulitzer-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=city-history">city-history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2265301818" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9237324022154284231">This is a long and engrossing book of the history of New York City. It is ever so readable and incredibly informative. Don&apos;t let its hefty 1400 pages be intimidating. Despite the wealth of detail, the writing is done with class and occasionally with humor. The topics of immigration, slavery, racism, feminism, the labor movement, and political corruption are all thoroughly covered. I can&apos;t wait to try reading the sequel, Greater Gotham, which features the same bulk but covers only from 1898-1919!</span>
  <span id="freeText9237324022154284231" style="display:none">This is a long and engrossing book of the history of New York City. It is ever so readable and incredibly informative. Don't let its hefty 1400 pages be intimidating. Despite the wealth of detail, the writing is done with class and occasionally with humor. The topics of immigration, slavery, racism, feminism, the labor movement, and political corruption are all thoroughly covered. I can't wait to try reading the sequel, Greater Gotham, which features the same bulk but covers only from 1898-1919!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9237324022154284231" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


