<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10346290973717869151">Edwin G. &quot;Ted&quot; Burrows was a Distinguished Professor of History at Brooklyn College. He received his B.A. from the University of Michigan in 1964, and his Ph.D. from Columbia University in 1973, where he studied under Eric McKitrick. He started teaching at Brooklyn College in 1973. He and historian Mike Wallace won the Pulitzer Prize for history in 1999 for <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/217329._Gotham__A_History_of_New_York_City_to_1898' title=' Gotham: A History of New York City to 1898' rel='nofollow noopener'> Gotham: A History of New York City to 1</a></span>
  <span id="freeText10346290973717869151" style="display:none">Edwin G. "Ted" Burrows was a Distinguished Professor of History at Brooklyn College. He received his B.A. from the University of Michigan in 1964, and his Ph.D. from Columbia University in 1973, where he studied under Eric McKitrick. He started teaching at Brooklyn College in 1973. He and historian Mike Wallace won the Pulitzer Prize for history in 1999 for <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/217329._Gotham__A_History_of_New_York_City_to_1898" title=" Gotham: A History of New York City to 1898" rel="nofollow noopener"> Gotham: A History of New York City to 1898</a>.</span>
